[SN]TITLE[SN]
Steven Davies: Rochdale bring in former Bradford City striker

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Rochdale have signed former Bradford City striker Steven Davies on a free transfer on a one-year deal.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 28-year-old was released by the Bantams in the summer after scoring five goals in his one-season stay.
He has also played for Blackpool, Bristol City, Derby and Tranmere.
"I've played with a few other players who have played at Rochdale under boss Keith Hill and they have all spoken highly about the club and the manager," he told the club website.
